@page "/"
@inject SwiftClientApiEndpoint Endpoint

<PageTitle>Sekiban Swift Sample</PageTitle>

<h1>Sekiban DCB Swift Sample</h1>

<p>
    This Blazor frontend talks to the Swift Hummingbird ClientApi running at
    <code>@Endpoint.BaseUrl</code>. The ClientApi in turn forwards reads + writes to the
    generic <code>Sekiban.Dcb.WasmRuntime.Host</code> (<code>wasmserver</code>) which
    loads the Swift-authored <code>sekiban-dcb-decider-swift.wasm</code> module for both
    MultiProjection and MaterializedView paths.
</p>

<h2>Available pages</h2>
<ul>
    <li><a href="mv">Materialized view status + classrooms/students/enrollments</a> — direct
        Postgres reads through the Swift <code>/api/mv/*</code> endpoints.</li>
    <li><a href="memory">In-memory projection</a> — MultiProjection reads through
        <code>/api/memory/classrooms</code>, resolved by wasmserver's
        <code>MultiProjectionGrain</code> using the Swift WASM projector.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Benchmark endpoints exposed by the Swift ClientApi</h2>
<p>
    The Rust/Go/TS/C# samples drive their benchmarks through the same shape, and Swift
    now exposes equivalent routes so this sample is a first-class matrix row:
</p>
<ul>
    <li><code>POST /api/rooms</code>, <code>POST /api/weatherforecast</code>,
        <code>POST /api/reservations/quick</code> — write path (constructs
        <code>SerializableCommitRequest</code> with tag-latest-sortable round-trips +
        multi-tag commit, matching the Rust handler).</li>
    <li><code>GET /api/rooms</code>, <code>GET /api/reservations</code>,
        <code>GET /api/reservations/by-room/{roomId}</code>,
        <code>GET /api/weatherforecast</code>,
        <code>GET /api/weatherforecast/count</code> — read path through the Swift WASM
        projectors (<code>RoomListProjection</code>,
        <code>WeatherForecastListProjection</code>,
        <code>ReservationListProjection</code>).</li>
</ul>
